  "title": "Composite-phase mechanoluminescent materials with adjustable color and intensity, and preparation method thereof",
  "abstract": "A composite-phase mechanoluminescent material with adjustable color and intensity, and a preparation method thereof. The material is prepared by using a ZnS-AOZnS composite phase as a matrix, performing ion exchange at an A-site and a Zn-site and co-doping with transition metal ions and rare earth ions. The chemical formula of the mechanoluminescent material is ZnS-AOZnS: xN, yM (0창혟짚x창혟짚1, 0창혟짚y창혟짚1), where N is a substitution element at the Zn-site and is one or more of Cu, Mn and Cr, M is a substitution element at the A-site and is one or more of Pr, Tb, Sm, Ho, Nd, Bi, Pb, Ag, Ti, Gd, Eu and Yb, A is one or more of Ca, Sr and Ba, and x and y represent molar percentages. The composite phase indicates that the matrix material prepared by compounding two phases by a high-temperature solid-state reaction method.",
